1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:03,253
I am Uhtred, son of Uhtred.

2
00:00:03,337 --> 00:00:06,173
After the battle at Tettenhall,

3
00:00:06,256 --> 00:00:08,800
Brida has been captured and enslaved

4
00:00:08,884 --> 00:00:10,427
in Wealas.

5
00:00:10,511 --> 00:00:14,556
Aethelred's death has left Mercia
with an empty throne

6
00:00:14,640 --> 00:00:16,600
and many vying for influence.

7
00:00:16,683 --> 00:00:19,186
As you know, Lady Aelfwynn is dear to me.

8
00:00:19,269 --> 00:00:22,314
I should like her to be betrothed
to a man I trust.

9
00:00:22,397 --> 00:00:24,608
Could you be such a man, Eardwulf?

10
00:00:24,691 --> 00:00:29,613
With Aelfwynn's hand in marriage,
Eardwulf was to become ruler of Mercia.

11
00:00:29,696 --> 00:00:34,243
They cast me aside,
treat my child as a bag of silver.

12
00:00:34,326 --> 00:00:38,956
But I was compelled fo disrupt their plans
and took Aelfwynn into hiding.

13
00:00:39,039 --> 00:00:40,916
Find me 12 men
to leave immediately.

14
00:00:40,999 --> 00:00:44,211
If Wessex is incapable,
we'll find the fugitives ourselves.

15
00:00:44,294 --> 00:00:46,755
Rumors of fever break out in the land...

16
00:00:46,838 --> 00:00:49,716
bringing fear and desperation.

17
00:00:49,800 --> 00:00:51,635
People are abandoning their villages.

18
00:00:51,718 --> 00:00:54,179
/f ravages worse
than any Dane invader.

19
00:00:54,263 --> 00:00:59,726
Two of my grandchildren travel
on open ground in time of sickness.

20
00:00:59,810 --> 00:01:02,771
Eadith betrayed her brother
fo protect Lady Aelfwynn.

21
00:01:02,854 --> 00:01:05,524
He murdered Lord Aethelred!
I witnessed it!

22
00:01:05,607 --> 00:01:09,486
But she has been struck by illness
and may not survive.

23
00:01:09,570 --> 00:01:11,029
I fear she's getting worse.

24
00:01:11,113 --> 00:01:14,825
We must return to Aegelesburyg,
reveal Eardwulfs treachery.

25
00:01:14,908 --> 00:01:17,327
And we tell him
what kind of a man he trusted.

26
00:01:17,411 --> 00:01:22,583
A new ruler must be found to bring peace,
or all will be lost.

27
00:01:23,166 --> 00:01:24,793
Destiny is all!

28
00:02:10,088 --> 00:02:14,384
In nomine Patris,
et Filii, et Spiritus Sancti...

29
00:02:16,011 --> 00:02:19,848
In nomine Patris, et Fill,
et Spiritus Sancti...

30
00:02:22,476 --> 00:02:24,061
In nomine Patris...

31
00:02:44,623 --> 00:02:47,292
- Ignore it.
- Such disrespect.

32
00:02:48,085 --> 00:02:51,296
I wasn't fond of Aethelred,
but he was Lord here.

33
00:02:51,380 --> 00:02:53,465
A curse upon the line of Aethelred!

34
00:03:07,646 --> 00:03:08,730
Quickly!

35
00:03:16,863 --> 00:03:19,741
- You will get me executed.
- You've survived so far.

36
00:03:19,825 --> 00:03:23,453
Can you hide them? She's my daughter.
And he's the King's bastard.

37
00:03:23,537 --> 00:03:24,788
- What?
- Do not ask.

38
00:03:24,871 --> 00:03:26,623
It is just until
I can get Edward to listen.

39
00:03:26,707 --> 00:03:30,544
I fear we are beyond that. This place
is like a tinder waiting for a spark.

40
00:03:30,627 --> 00:03:34,131
Which is why I need you to help me.

41
00:03:34,214 --> 00:03:35,298
Thank you.

42
00:03:35,757 --> 00:03:36,925
Come on, this way.

43
00:03:41,096 --> 00:03:43,223
Curse upon the line of Aethelred!

44
00:03:44,391 --> 00:03:46,518
Is this defiance caused by hunger?

45
00:03:47,436 --> 00:03:50,897
Hunger, fever, a lack of leadership.

46
00:03:51,732 --> 00:03:53,233
How long will the grain last?

47
00:03:54,401 --> 00:03:58,155
That depends on how much
the Ealdormen have kept for themselves.

48
00:04:00,699 --> 00:04:02,075
May God forgive you!

49
00:04:04,327 --> 00:04:08,373
Lord Burgred speaks against me yet again.

50
00:04:09,374 --> 00:04:10,792
Ignore the chatter.

51
00:04:11,877 --> 00:04:15,338
Truly dangerous men do not issue threats.

52
00:04:20,886 --> 00:04:21,970
Look at them.

53
00:04:22,846 --> 00:04:26,683
I know that look. You have no plan.

54
00:04:29,060 --> 00:04:30,353
I have a plan.

55
00:04:30,437 --> 00:04:31,563
Shame on you!

56
00:04:32,981 --> 00:04:35,317
We tell the Ealdorman
we'll kill their lord.

57
00:04:38,278 --> 00:04:39,863
Forgive me, but there is news.

58
00:04:41,406 --> 00:04:44,034
The Ealdormen have called their Witan
for after the funeral.

59
00:04:44,659 --> 00:04:46,161
Why was I not informed?

60
00:04:46,745 --> 00:04:50,791
They say you do not need to know
and that you may not enter the Witan.

61
00:04:53,293 --> 00:04:57,547
Pater noster qui es in caéelis.

62
00:04:58,799 --> 00:05:01,009
May your name be hallowed.

63
00:05:01,718 --> 00:05:03,512
May your will be done...

64
00:05:05,013 --> 00:05:06,348
What has happened here?

65
00:05:08,725 --> 00:05:14,397
- Slaughter, betrayal and now ambition.
- So, when they come to kill you,

66
00:05:14,481 --> 00:05:17,275
- what would you like me to do?
- They will not kill me.

67
00:05:17,984 --> 00:05:20,445
I am the only one
who knows where Aelfwynn hides.

68
00:05:21,488 --> 00:05:23,073
We will strike a deal.

69
00:05:23,156 --> 00:05:25,700
The King cannot be trusted.

70
00:05:25,784 --> 00:05:27,869
He calls himself leader of all Saxons,

71
00:05:27,953 --> 00:05:30,956
yet he-he schemes against us
to make us submissive!

72
00:05:31,039 --> 00:05:32,707
We will ask him to explain himself.

73
00:05:32,791 --> 00:05:35,961
So he can lie about Lady Aelfwynn,
as he lied about her mother?

74
00:05:36,044 --> 00:05:40,131
- The time has come to take a bolder step!
- Isolating ourselves from Wessex

75
00:05:40,215 --> 00:05:42,926
would serve Mercia no better
than King Edward's tyranny!

76
00:05:43,009 --> 00:05:46,847
- Then let us put it to the Witan!
- Who would...

77
00:05:52,602 --> 00:05:54,104
Please, continue.

78
00:05:55,939 --> 00:06:00,819
- The Witan is closed to all but Mercians.
- I am Mercian in blood through my mother.

79
00:06:00,902 --> 00:06:03,154
Lord, no. We must be able to speak freely.

80
00:06:03,238 --> 00:06:04,698
I do not deny that.

81
00:06:12,831 --> 00:06:16,334
Speak. I come merely to listen
to your discussions.

82
00:06:16,418 --> 00:06:20,046
You were saying I lied
about Lady Aelfwynn?

83
00:06:20,130 --> 00:06:23,341
Everyone knows
Eardwulf hunts her on the road.

84
00:06:23,425 --> 00:06:25,510
Yes, to bring her here to safety.

85
00:06:25,594 --> 00:06:29,389
We are waiting until the sickness passes
and Eardwulf and Lady Aelfwynn return.

86
00:06:29,472 --> 00:06:30,515
Lies!

87
00:06:31,725 --> 00:06:34,936
That seems an unwise thing to say.

88
00:06:35,020 --> 00:06:40,984
You said we could speak freely,
and I say this is lies!

89
00:06:42,277 --> 00:06:44,446
Lord Burgred, remember who I am.

90
00:06:44,529 --> 00:06:49,618
You move in your troops,
leader of the Mercian Guard disappears,

91
00:06:49,701 --> 00:06:52,662
so yet again we cannot defend ourselves.

92
00:06:52,746 --> 00:06:57,042
Then suddenly, from nowhere,
a fever closes the city

93
00:06:57,125 --> 00:06:59,794
- and starves the people!
- Burgred! You go too far!

94
00:06:59,878 --> 00:07:02,881
You cannot be suggesting
I created this situation.

95
00:07:02,964 --> 00:07:06,968
The people are hungry
because you hoard the grain!

96
00:07:07,052 --> 00:07:10,388
We hoard it
so it cannot fatten Wessex fighters.

97
00:07:10,472 --> 00:07:13,058
Enough! Enough!

98
00:07:13,141 --> 00:07:15,101
- The outlaw returns!
- No outlaw.

99
00:07:15,185 --> 00:07:18,313
Just a man who's seen enough conflict
in Mercia. Let me speak.

100
00:07:20,899 --> 00:07:23,485
I am Lord Uhtred,
who, with Lady Aethelflaed,

101
00:07:23,568 --> 00:07:27,405
has led Mercian fyrds to victory
against the Danes at Tettenhall.

102
00:07:27,781 --> 00:07:30,951
I spilled blood for you.
I ask that you listen to me in return.

103
00:07:31,034 --> 00:07:33,536
Lord Uhtred, explain to these people.

104
00:07:33,620 --> 00:07:36,414
Lady Aelfwynn is safe
and about to return for her betrothal.

105
00:07:36,498 --> 00:07:39,084
She is safe, but she cannot be betrothed.

106
00:07:40,293 --> 00:07:43,964
Eardwulf has confessed
to the murder of Lord Aethelred

107
00:07:44,047 --> 00:07:45,840
and he has fled Mercia.

108
00:07:45,924 --> 00:07:48,510
Ignore the heathen!
He's just a troublemaker!

109
00:07:48,593 --> 00:07:52,389
Why do you seek to humiliate Mercia
with these outrageous lies?

110
00:07:52,472 --> 00:07:56,059
It is no lie. Eardwulf has
near confessed it before his men.

111
00:07:56,142 --> 00:07:57,894
This was found on him.

112
00:07:59,688 --> 00:08:02,899
It belonged to Lord Aethelred
and was stolen from his dying hand.

113
00:08:07,696 --> 00:08:09,823
Eardwulf has done many things
to harm Mercia.

114
00:08:09,906 --> 00:08:12,492
You all chose to turn your eyes from it.

115
00:08:12,575 --> 00:08:14,035
This is the consequence.

116
00:08:41,855 --> 00:08:42,939
What is it?

117
00:08:43,773 --> 00:08:46,151
- I'm not going to tell you.
- Is it wormwood?

118
00:08:49,279 --> 00:08:52,657
It will not work. I've heard it kills men.

119
00:08:52,741 --> 00:08:54,701
Poison can sometimes be a cure.

120
00:08:55,160 --> 00:08:57,203
Mixed with holy water,
it will cool the fever.

121
00:08:58,496 --> 00:09:00,874
Look at her. She is dying.

122
00:09:00,957 --> 00:09:05,170
- If she does, we will be blamed.
- There's sickness everywhere, Eadith.

123
00:09:05,253 --> 00:09:09,549
Yes, and who gets accused?
Sinners, people like me.

124
00:09:10,425 --> 00:09:12,052
You have not been shunned as I have.

125
00:09:12,844 --> 00:09:14,596
I will not take the risk.

126
00:09:15,930 --> 00:09:18,600
And I thought
you were amongst the bravest of warriors.

127
00:09:27,025 --> 00:09:28,068
There.

128
00:09:29,194 --> 00:09:30,904
Now she and I are both doomed.

129
00:09:35,909 --> 00:09:37,035
Aelfwynn?

130
00:09:46,211 --> 00:09:49,547
Where is my niece, Uhtred?

131
00:09:49,631 --> 00:09:52,842
We know you traveled the road
with children from Saltwic.

132
00:09:55,762 --> 00:09:57,680
- Where are they?
- I will not tell you.

133
00:09:58,807 --> 00:10:02,852
Not until I have your word that Aelfwynn
and Lady Aethelflaed will be protected.

134
00:10:02,936 --> 00:10:04,813
You are in no position to bargain!

135
00:10:06,022 --> 00:10:08,525
So, I will ask you this one more time.

136
00:10:09,818 --> 00:10:11,694
Where is my niece?

137
00:10:13,905 --> 00:10:16,783
Tell me or I shall have you seized.

138
00:10:16,866 --> 00:10:19,369
I've done nothing wrong. You know this.

139
00:10:19,452 --> 00:10:23,832
Your actions have caused chaos,
disturbed a smooth transition of power

140
00:10:23,915 --> 00:10:26,251
and launched an uprising
amongst the Ealdormen!

141
00:10:27,752 --> 00:10:31,131
So, even you will understand
why I call you traitor.

142
00:10:33,883 --> 00:10:34,968
Take him away.

143
00:10:45,603 --> 00:10:49,732
Find out where he hides her. The girl
is our only way to maintain the alliance.

144
00:10:49,816 --> 00:10:51,901
If we cannot betroth her,
we lose that bond.

145
00:10:53,319 --> 00:10:55,405
But who to betroth her to?

146
00:10:56,281 --> 00:10:59,242
You said there are no suitable candidates.

147
00:10:59,325 --> 00:11:00,577
Yes.

148
00:11:01,995 --> 00:11:05,498
Perhaps instead of seeking
to make a bond with the Ealdormen...

149
00:11:06,708 --> 00:11:08,543
we should find a way to break them.

150
00:11:13,047 --> 00:11:16,259
Why haven't we slaughtered them?

151
00:11:16,342 --> 00:11:19,053
- We were tricked!
- You say you have them under control,

152
00:11:19,137 --> 00:11:21,681
and then I hear they've taken
our villages to the south!

153
00:11:21,764 --> 00:11:23,433
I've never seen men like this before.

154
00:11:23,516 --> 00:11:27,645
I do not want this news to reach
my brother whilst he's on holy pilgrimage.

155
00:11:28,688 --> 00:11:31,608
- You will tell no one of these defeats.
- They are terrifying.

156
00:11:34,402 --> 00:11:35,445
What was that?

157
00:11:38,615 --> 00:11:40,241
Are you thirsty?

158
00:12:10,730 --> 00:12:12,774
Stay back! Come on, move aside.

159
00:12:12,857 --> 00:12:16,778
We are taking it to storage,
so that Wessex cannot steal it.

160
00:12:16,861 --> 00:12:18,238
Seize the carts!

161
00:12:18,321 --> 00:12:21,741
The King demands the grain
be shared fairly amongst the people.

162
00:12:21,824 --> 00:12:24,160
The King does not care for the people.

163
00:12:29,499 --> 00:12:30,583
Guards!

164
00:12:31,834 --> 00:12:33,711
Stand aside!

165
00:12:41,844 --> 00:12:42,887
With me!

166
00:12:48,643 --> 00:12:50,812
I would call this provocation.

167
00:13:02,991 --> 00:13:04,158
What is it?

168
00:13:04,242 --> 00:13:06,494
We're being followed. Come on!

169
00:13:06,577 --> 00:13:07,662
Go!

170
00:13:24,387 --> 00:13:26,514
Could we have been discovered?

171
00:13:26,597 --> 00:13:29,142
We cannot outrun them.

172
00:13:29,225 --> 00:13:31,978
We must hide. Hyah! Away!

173
00:13:56,210 --> 00:13:57,253
Lord King!

174
00:13:57,337 --> 00:14:01,424
Why do you continue to impound our grain
and occupy our citadel?

175
00:14:01,507 --> 00:14:06,512
May I remind you, this hall is only for
the Lord of Mercia and his Ealdormen!

176
00:14:06,596 --> 00:14:09,682
And so I shall remain here
until the new Lord is chosen.

177
00:14:09,766 --> 00:14:14,228
Yet the Witan are minded
to separate from Wessex.

178
00:14:14,312 --> 00:14:15,396
Really?

179
00:14:20,693 --> 00:14:23,571
You do not speak for the Ealdormen.

180
00:14:23,654 --> 00:14:26,199
You are merely grasping
like a greedy child,

181
00:14:26,282 --> 00:14:27,867
and I shall not indulge it.

182
00:14:27,950 --> 00:14:30,370
If you want me to leave the hall,

183
00:14:30,453 --> 00:14:35,124
one of your men
will have to lay hands on a King,

184
00:14:35,208 --> 00:14:41,255
a man anointed by God
to rule in his name and a son of Alfred.

185
00:14:42,548 --> 00:14:44,300
They dishonor me,

186
00:14:44,384 --> 00:14:48,930
you dishonor Mercia for breaking
the accord so long held between us.

187
00:14:50,223 --> 00:14:52,975
Who will be the man to do it?

188
00:14:53,476 --> 00:14:56,020
Drag a King through the hall?

189
00:14:56,104 --> 00:15:00,024
Who dares throw himself
before God like this?

190
00:15:04,987 --> 00:15:06,322
I will.

191
00:15:10,368 --> 00:15:11,911
I will fight for Mercia.

192
00:15:13,204 --> 00:15:16,749
You forget I am King
and wield power like a King.

193
00:15:23,548 --> 00:15:24,924
Lord Burgred...

194
00:15:26,884 --> 00:15:30,596
we have taken your son to Wessex
for religious instruction.

195
00:15:35,810 --> 00:15:40,231
He will be cared for
until his father finds better judgment.

196
00:16:06,674 --> 00:16:08,384
- Lady Aethelflaed.
- Run.

197
00:16:08,468 --> 00:16:10,470
- We know you're there!
- I'll hold them off.

198
00:16:10,553 --> 00:16:11,804
No, no!

199
00:16:18,269 --> 00:16:19,312
Sihtric!

200
00:16:22,523 --> 00:16:23,983
Lady, it's Uhtred's men!

201
00:16:27,195 --> 00:16:28,946
- Thank God it's you.
- My lady.

202
00:16:29,697 --> 00:16:30,781
Aldhelm.

203
00:16:32,950 --> 00:16:34,327
You are not easy to find.

204
00:16:34,410 --> 00:16:35,745
Did Uhtred send you?

205
00:16:36,662 --> 00:16:38,247
What news of my daughter?

206
00:16:39,123 --> 00:16:42,168
She is safe.
Uhtred has returned to Aegelesburg

207
00:16:42,251 --> 00:16:45,379
- to bargain for your protection.
- Is Aelfwynn with him?

208
00:16:49,634 --> 00:16:53,763
She is being cared for,
but... she became unwell.

209
00:16:54,222 --> 00:16:56,599
- The sickness?
- It may not be.

210
00:16:57,350 --> 00:16:59,352
She's traveled a great distance.

211
00:17:00,603 --> 00:17:01,646
Take me to her.

212
00:17:09,862 --> 00:17:11,614
Did the King ask you to do this?

213
00:17:12,907 --> 00:17:14,033
Do not speak.

214
00:17:14,116 --> 00:17:18,037
Were you sworn to Alfred?
Where will we have met?

215
00:17:22,625 --> 00:17:24,377
We have fought at Beamfleot.

216
00:17:35,930 --> 00:17:40,518
Must we extract this information
from you the hard way?

217
00:17:50,361 --> 00:17:54,949
Can't you just tell us
where Lady Aelfwynn is hiding?

218
00:18:00,413 --> 00:18:01,664
It's your choice.

219
00:18:01,688 --> 00:18:09,688
http://hiqve.com/

220
00:19:00,264 --> 00:19:01,307
Aelfwynn?

221
00:19:01,849 --> 00:19:03,225
Aelfwynn?

222
00:19:04,977 --> 00:19:07,396
Aelfwynn, please wake up. Aelfwynn...

223
00:19:07,480 --> 00:19:08,648
You've killed her.

224
00:19:08,731 --> 00:19:12,276
No. Perhaps it is the poison
burning the fever in her body?

225
00:19:12,360 --> 00:19:15,655
- Or perhaps she's dead!
- No. No, she's still breathing.

226
00:19:18,741 --> 00:19:23,329
We must take her to a place of-of comfort.
Let us go back to Aegelesburg.

227
00:19:23,412 --> 00:19:25,612
- No, but Lord Uhtred said...
- I know what Uhtred said.

228
00:19:26,207 --> 00:19:29,001
But Uhtred is not my master
and we cannot stay here.

229
00:19:30,544 --> 00:19:34,507
We must get her to a healer in Aegelesburg
if she is to stand a chance.

230
00:19:37,051 --> 00:19:38,177
Okay.

231
00:19:42,556 --> 00:19:44,100
Lord have mercy on us.

232
00:20:05,287 --> 00:20:07,415
How are your expressions of piety?

233
00:20:08,874 --> 00:20:10,042
Full-hearted.

234
00:20:11,711 --> 00:20:13,462
Where is Burgred's son?

235
00:20:14,130 --> 00:20:15,256
He is safe.

236
00:20:17,174 --> 00:20:21,345
It was a callous decision,
but I suspect a clever one.

237
00:20:22,263 --> 00:20:25,558
It has diminished Burgred
and you have averted a fight.

238
00:20:26,559 --> 00:20:28,519
For that, I am grateful.

239
00:20:29,395 --> 00:20:31,439
I do not think the conflict is over.

240
00:20:31,522 --> 00:20:35,484
But you've been decisive,
and that will help in times of chaos.

241
00:20:36,652 --> 00:20:41,073
Now you could play peacemaker yourself.
How will you proceed?

242
00:20:41,157 --> 00:20:44,160
I will not tell you,
for you will not keep it to yourself.

243
00:20:46,078 --> 00:20:47,621
Then I will tell you one thing.

244
00:20:48,414 --> 00:20:52,793
The people of Mercia are Saxon,
but they will never be of Wessex.

245
00:20:53,377 --> 00:20:56,297
Force them to be,
and they will fight back.

246
00:20:56,380 --> 00:21:00,342
If you do not seek to conquer,
all will be resolved.

247
00:21:00,968 --> 00:21:03,012
Continue to care for Mercia,

248
00:21:03,095 --> 00:21:07,308
find the right match for my granddaughter,
and peace will come.

249
00:21:08,267 --> 00:21:13,063
Did we discover if Uhtred
has all the children from Saltwic?

250
00:21:13,147 --> 00:21:16,066
He will not give us that information.

251
00:21:16,150 --> 00:21:18,277
Believe me, we tried to extract it.

252
00:21:53,270 --> 00:21:57,775
Don't turn away from me.
This was done in your name.

253
00:21:57,858 --> 00:22:00,986
I did not order this, Uhtred.

254
00:22:08,536 --> 00:22:10,871
Aethelhelm claims he acts for you.

255
00:22:13,457 --> 00:22:14,500
Look at me!

256
00:22:31,267 --> 00:22:33,769
Fetch him food and water
and furs to keep him warm.

257
00:22:33,853 --> 00:22:34,895
Yes, Lord.

258
00:22:37,773 --> 00:22:41,193
I did not order this,
because I knew it would not work.

259
00:22:42,611 --> 00:22:46,574
Lord Aethelhelm was foolish
to think you would weaken.

260
00:22:54,331 --> 00:22:58,961
Tell me, where does it come from,
this courage?

261
00:23:00,546 --> 00:23:04,884
You have suffered greatly, and for what?
A child you barely know?

262
00:23:04,967 --> 00:23:06,176
Not for her.

263
00:23:07,011 --> 00:23:08,095
Then why?

264
00:23:08,178 --> 00:23:10,514
The same reason I fought at Tettenhall.

265
00:23:12,433 --> 00:23:15,352
My deep love of Mercian politics.

266
00:23:19,815 --> 00:23:21,275
You love my sister.

267
00:23:26,405 --> 00:23:30,492
Your sister is a widow.
She has my respect.

268
00:23:37,708 --> 00:23:41,837
I've always envied you
for choosing your own path.

269
00:23:42,421 --> 00:23:44,465
Looked at the way men followed you

270
00:23:44,548 --> 00:23:50,012
and felt... inspired,
if somewhat grudgingly.

271
00:23:52,556 --> 00:23:56,435
And now I wonder
if you are as imprisoned as I am...

272
00:23:57,353 --> 00:24:02,274
unable to escape a life
that was imposed upon you.

273
00:24:02,358 --> 00:24:04,234
Neither of us asked to be here.

274
00:24:05,069 --> 00:24:08,113
For my part,
the choices are growing narrower.

275
00:24:09,657 --> 00:24:12,242
I have tried to find a solution here

276
00:24:12,326 --> 00:24:15,204
that respects the Mercians
and keeps order.

277
00:24:16,413 --> 00:24:18,457
But events have turned against me...

278
00:24:19,959 --> 00:24:25,089
and I have to ask myself,
does God want me to fight for this?

279
00:24:27,424 --> 00:24:29,843
I have followed the guidance of others
too long.

280
00:24:30,469 --> 00:24:32,888
I have made mistakes, yes.

281
00:24:35,474 --> 00:24:38,310
I have lived somewhat in Alfred's shadow.

282
00:24:43,691 --> 00:24:46,026
And now you see the light?

283
00:24:51,156 --> 00:24:55,786
I know he was speaking the truth when
he said the kingdoms are stronger united.

284
00:24:59,581 --> 00:25:02,710
So, perhaps
I should be unifying them myself...

285
00:25:04,003 --> 00:25:06,463
rather than making a child do it for me.

286
00:25:11,885 --> 00:25:13,595
You are free to go, Uhtred.

287
00:25:21,895 --> 00:25:23,981
Return to Aelfwynn.

288
00:25:24,690 --> 00:25:30,112
Reunite with my sister and keep them safe
until the conflict passes.

289
00:25:30,195 --> 00:25:34,033
Matters may grow ugly here.
It is best they do not see it.

290
00:26:02,936 --> 00:26:04,730
You learn something every day...

291
00:26:04,813 --> 00:26:09,276
They'll be pushed back
to the sea, drowning in their own blood!

292
00:26:09,359 --> 00:26:11,570
Picked on the wrong men this time!

293
00:26:13,781 --> 00:26:14,823
Hey!

294
00:26:15,949 --> 00:26:17,326
Did you hear that, bitch?

295
00:26:17,409 --> 00:26:19,661
Do you want to congratulate us?

296
00:26:19,745 --> 00:26:23,373
Oh, she cannot speak for thirst.

297
00:26:24,083 --> 00:26:26,251
Hey, want a drink?

298
00:26:27,336 --> 00:26:29,755
Come on. Come on.

299
00:27:16,760 --> 00:27:19,972
She says your daughter passed
into the next life.

300
00:27:22,516 --> 00:27:24,518
And her body was taken to Aegelesburg.

301
00:27:49,710 --> 00:27:54,298
Has Uhtred finally realized
the stupidity of his defiance?

302
00:27:54,381 --> 00:27:55,549
I would say not.

303
00:27:56,091 --> 00:27:58,844
But I have asked him to leave Aegelesburg.

304
00:27:59,720 --> 00:28:02,890
- And I would like you to do the same.
- Lord?

305
00:28:02,973 --> 00:28:06,476
More than once
you have taken it upon yourself

306
00:28:06,560 --> 00:28:10,856
to interpret my wishes
in a way that I find unchristian.

307
00:28:10,939 --> 00:28:14,109
I have tried to guide you
on a bolder course.

308
00:28:14,193 --> 00:28:17,446
Is it boldness to confine a widow?

309
00:28:17,988 --> 00:28:19,489
Beat a man as he was chained?

310
00:28:19,573 --> 00:28:24,536
I simply placed myself between you
and some necessary unpleasantness.

311
00:28:24,620 --> 00:28:27,414
- I did what you asked.
- But not what I wanted.

312
00:28:28,290 --> 00:28:32,294
Once again, you used my orders
to suit your own wishes.

313
00:28:32,920 --> 00:28:37,424
Perhaps being so far from home
has clouded your judgment.

314
00:28:38,091 --> 00:28:40,219
Return to Winchester,
and all will be well.

315
00:28:40,636 --> 00:28:42,554
Very well, I shall do as you request.

316
00:28:46,934 --> 00:28:49,937
I hope your mother
advises you better than I have.

317
00:28:53,232 --> 00:28:57,236
Wonderful news, Edward! The word is that
Aelfwynn has been brought to the gates.

318
00:28:58,111 --> 00:28:59,238
She is here?

319
00:28:59,321 --> 00:29:02,157
- Shall I bring her into the town?
- Yes, of course! Bring her to me!

320
00:29:03,450 --> 00:29:04,493
Open the gate!

321
00:29:04,576 --> 00:29:08,747
See? It is a sign!
The Lord did not want you to be a tyrant

322
00:29:08,830 --> 00:29:10,457
and now has sent you your reward!

323
00:29:10,540 --> 00:29:13,418
Move, move!

324
00:29:17,130 --> 00:29:20,425
Oh, dear God!
We will need a priest.

325
00:29:20,509 --> 00:29:23,303
We've tried everything.
She needs the final rites, Lord.

326
00:29:24,346 --> 00:29:27,599
Find me every healer in town.
Do not speak a word of this to anyone.

327
00:29:27,683 --> 00:29:29,184
Yes, Lord. Come with me.

328
00:29:29,643 --> 00:29:30,686
Go.

329
00:29:31,937 --> 00:29:33,397
Do you think she will survive?

330
00:29:48,287 --> 00:29:50,622
Dear God!

331
00:29:51,790 --> 00:29:53,458
I'll find the man who did this.

332
00:29:55,585 --> 00:29:57,671
Eh, don't, don't, don't.

333
00:29:57,754 --> 00:30:00,507
What now?

334
00:30:01,633 --> 00:30:04,636
There's nothing for us here, Finan.
Where's my daughter?

335
00:30:04,720 --> 00:30:08,390
She's insisting on helping Father Pyrlig,
and I've tried to dissuade her, but...

336
00:30:08,473 --> 00:30:10,809
She is too stubborn
because she is my daughter?

337
00:30:13,562 --> 00:30:14,646
Where is she?

338
00:30:31,496 --> 00:30:33,707
The King continues to take the town.

339
00:30:34,916 --> 00:30:36,335
He feeds the people.

340
00:30:36,418 --> 00:30:38,587
Truly, you have lost your judgment.

341
00:30:40,672 --> 00:30:42,007
Think on your son!

342
00:30:43,383 --> 00:30:45,177
- There's grain!
- Come with me.

343
00:30:46,178 --> 00:30:47,346
The cart's here!

344
00:30:48,764 --> 00:30:51,141
- Okay, there's plenty to go around.
- Form a line.

345
00:30:51,224 --> 00:30:53,894
Don't push!

346
00:30:53,977 --> 00:30:56,563
Here.

347
00:30:57,230 --> 00:30:59,524
Stand back and form a line!

348
00:31:00,609 --> 00:31:02,569
- You don't need it!
- Hold on!

349
00:31:02,652 --> 00:31:04,696
You would think the grain was silver.

350
00:31:06,073 --> 00:31:09,493
Hey, calm yourselves. Calm yourselves!
There's more than enough.

351
00:31:09,576 --> 00:31:11,203
- Stop this!
- Stand back!

352
00:31:11,286 --> 00:31:13,747
- Get off me!
- Get off!

353
00:31:17,542 --> 00:31:18,752
Stiorra!

354
00:31:25,050 --> 00:31:27,844
Finan, take Stiorra!

355
00:31:27,928 --> 00:31:31,723
- Look at me. You're fine.
- Stop! Drop it!

356
00:31:33,141 --> 00:31:35,852
Enough! Get back!

357
00:31:42,984 --> 00:31:46,363
I know you suffer, but turning
on each other will not save you!

358
00:31:47,864 --> 00:31:52,327
You must work as one
rather than quarreling amongst yourselves.

359
00:31:53,078 --> 00:31:55,580
Now, get back behind the cart
and form a line.

360
00:31:55,664 --> 00:31:57,541
Each person will be given what they need.

361
00:31:57,624 --> 00:32:00,627
- Look how he influences them.
- Trust me.

362
00:32:01,044 --> 00:32:05,257
- He will make them rise against you.
- Mercian must not fight Mercian.

363
00:32:06,091 --> 00:32:08,468
Anyone who wants grain
must keep the peace.

364
00:32:09,678 --> 00:32:12,472
- Finan, help me with the bags.
- Lord.

365
00:32:15,976 --> 00:32:17,227
Bring him before me.

366
00:32:21,690 --> 00:32:22,732
Bless you.

367
00:32:22,816 --> 00:32:24,067
Thank you.

368
00:33:19,122 --> 00:33:21,750
Kill anyone
who looks like they cannot work!

369
00:33:22,209 --> 00:33:26,087
Fat ones we can sell as slaves.

370
00:33:45,273 --> 00:33:47,067
Secure the fort!

371
00:34:03,166 --> 00:34:04,376
Spare him!

372
00:34:06,419 --> 00:34:07,796
You want the silver?

373
00:34:09,965 --> 00:34:11,800
I have no interest in silver.

374
00:34:24,104 --> 00:34:26,273
We are looking for a Dane named Brida.

375
00:34:26,731 --> 00:34:29,651
Too late. I killed her.

376
00:34:30,986 --> 00:34:32,487
You did not!

377
00:34:49,421 --> 00:34:52,966
Lord King,
I was leaving as we agreed.

378
00:34:53,049 --> 00:34:56,553
But then you chose to be part
of a disturbance in the town.

379
00:34:56,636 --> 00:34:58,763
I did not choose to be part of it.

380
00:34:59,472 --> 00:35:02,642
You were just guided by forces
beyond your control?

381
00:35:03,393 --> 00:35:06,438
As ever,
Uhtred is but a plaything of his gods.

382
00:35:13,153 --> 00:35:15,989
You wanted to bring peace
to Aegelesburg.

383
00:35:17,240 --> 00:35:20,118
Which is better than wanting
to start another battle.

384
00:35:20,201 --> 00:35:22,662
You truly think I seek battles?

385
00:35:22,746 --> 00:35:27,250
Perhaps not, but that is what will happen.
The Ealdormen will not back down,

386
00:35:27,334 --> 00:35:30,462
so you will finish the slaughter
that the Danes have started.

387
00:35:30,545 --> 00:35:31,713
I fear you are right.

388
00:35:32,756 --> 00:35:35,008
There is a risk of great slaughter.

389
00:35:35,091 --> 00:35:36,718
Innocent people will suffer.

390
00:35:36,801 --> 00:35:40,847
I will crush them, leave the town
in the care of the Wessex Guard.

391
00:35:41,306 --> 00:35:43,266
They will run the place
as they feel they need to,

392
00:35:43,350 --> 00:35:45,852
which is rarely an easy life
for the people, is it?

393
00:35:47,228 --> 00:35:49,481
Strange things happen
in times of conflict.

394
00:35:50,273 --> 00:35:53,818
The Ealdormen are passionate
that they could repel us for a while.

395
00:35:53,902 --> 00:35:56,988
Whichever way,
the conflict would continue.

396
00:35:58,657 --> 00:36:00,909
They might try to hunt down my sister.

397
00:36:02,369 --> 00:36:03,787
They would not find her.

398
00:36:03,870 --> 00:36:07,248
So you will live as fugitives for months,
years? Is that how you see it?

399
00:36:07,332 --> 00:36:08,958
I've spent many years on the road.

400
00:36:09,042 --> 00:36:11,419
True, but it is not the life
that was meant for Aethelflaed.

401
00:36:11,503 --> 00:36:14,673
- Hardly what she deserves.
- That is a choice you are making.

402
00:36:18,385 --> 00:36:24,265
If I place someone to rule here
who might forge a path to peace,

403
00:36:24,349 --> 00:36:27,102
someone who might not
necessarily please the Ealdormen,

404
00:36:27,185 --> 00:36:30,897
but whose popularity with the people
might force them to accept it...

405
00:36:32,440 --> 00:36:37,529
Let us call him a Lord and Protector
who would rule here

406
00:36:37,612 --> 00:36:41,032
just for a few years
until things are less volatile.

407
00:36:44,160 --> 00:36:48,123
I wondered if that person should be you.

408
00:36:52,419 --> 00:36:53,461
Me?

409
00:36:59,968 --> 00:37:01,886
I do not want to rule here.

410
00:37:01,970 --> 00:37:05,265
Yes, but as we know,
you rarely get to make your own choices.

411
00:37:06,891 --> 00:37:11,896
Find an equilibrium,
wait for an Ealdorman to come of age,

412
00:37:11,980 --> 00:37:15,483
if my niece survives, betroth her
to someone Aethelflaed chooses.

413
00:37:15,567 --> 00:37:20,363
It is clear to me
you have the respect of the people here.

414
00:37:20,947 --> 00:37:22,115
They listen to you.

415
00:37:23,366 --> 00:37:26,327
So, perhaps we should use that
to our mutual advantage.

416
00:37:26,411 --> 00:37:27,912
I do not seek advantage.

417
00:37:27,996 --> 00:37:29,539
Even to bring peace?

418
00:37:30,331 --> 00:37:33,877
You accept,
you ensure Mercia returns to how it was,

419
00:37:33,960 --> 00:37:36,546
before Aethelred destroyed everything.

420
00:37:36,629 --> 00:37:40,091
- If I do not?
- As you said, there will be slaughter.

421
00:37:41,134 --> 00:37:43,511
And that will be a choice you are making.

422
00:37:46,306 --> 00:37:49,267
Accept and your reputation
will be restored

423
00:37:49,350 --> 00:37:51,728
and your men given status and wealth.

424
00:37:53,313 --> 00:37:57,233
And in a few years, you will be free
to pursue whichever dreams you may have.

425
00:37:58,109 --> 00:38:02,405
I could give you the troops you need
to retake the fortress you lost.

426
00:38:06,743 --> 00:38:08,244
And in return?

427
00:38:08,787 --> 00:38:11,998
I would be your King
and expect your loyalty.

428
00:38:20,632 --> 00:38:22,634
I expect an answer by tomorrow.

429
00:38:52,163 --> 00:38:53,957
How do I know you are Brida?

430
00:38:55,041 --> 00:38:59,254
I fought with Guthrum.
I followed Ragnar.

431
00:38:59,337 --> 00:39:00,964
I killed men at Tettenhall...

432
00:39:01,047 --> 00:39:05,468
So, you have heard of Saxon battles.
That does not make you Brida.

433
00:39:16,938 --> 00:39:19,440
It is Cnut's babe you carry,
or that of a Welshman?

434
00:39:21,150 --> 00:39:25,530
The babe was made by Cnut,
but Cnut's fallen.

435
00:39:27,991 --> 00:39:29,659
I do not know you.

436
00:39:30,827 --> 00:39:34,289
Cnut's cousin, Sigtryggr of Irland.

437
00:39:34,372 --> 00:39:36,916
Sigtryggr was defeated and killed.

438
00:39:37,000 --> 00:39:40,837
Defeated, yes,
driven from his settlements, yes.

439
00:39:41,671 --> 00:39:44,632
But at this moment, quite alive.

440
00:39:48,803 --> 00:39:53,808
- And who do you belong to now, Brida?
- No man. I am a warrior alone.

441
00:39:53,892 --> 00:39:56,019
You do not look like a warrior.

442
00:39:57,020 --> 00:39:59,188
Give me your sword and I will show you.

443
00:39:59,272 --> 00:40:02,442
Give you my sword? You might kill me.

444
00:40:03,359 --> 00:40:08,031
No, the Brida I have heard of
is cunning, so I will stay armed.

445
00:40:09,616 --> 00:40:12,911
If you are who you say you are,
then show me.

446
00:40:34,807 --> 00:40:37,769
Listen to me. Talk.

447
00:40:42,273 --> 00:40:47,236
Prepare to be broken,
as you tried to break me.

448
00:40:59,207 --> 00:41:04,629
Bridal!
You have the anger of a she-wolf!

449
00:41:12,595 --> 00:41:14,430
- Is he joking?
- No.

450
00:41:16,391 --> 00:41:20,478
So, he's either lost his mind,
or he's a genius like his father.

451
00:41:20,561 --> 00:41:25,316
He says that Aethelflaed will be defended.
And it is true.

452
00:41:26,109 --> 00:41:28,903
No other leader in Mercia
would protect her like I would.

453
00:41:29,529 --> 00:41:30,571
But?

454
00:41:31,280 --> 00:41:33,574
But I was not born
to be the Lord of Mercia.

455
00:41:33,658 --> 00:41:35,368
I never sought that kind of power.

456
00:41:35,451 --> 00:41:38,037
Well, perhaps that in itself
makes you the best man.

457
00:41:39,539 --> 00:41:42,125
Mercia has suffered
from being led by ambition.

458
00:41:43,876 --> 00:41:47,588
So, apart from the silver and the power

459
00:41:47,672 --> 00:41:51,467
and saving the woman you love,
what is holding you back?

460
00:41:51,551 --> 00:41:55,722
Giving my loyalty to another Saxon king.
I swore to myself I would not do that.

461
00:41:55,805 --> 00:41:59,642
I swear I will not drink too much ale,
and I frequently go back on my word.

462
00:42:03,938 --> 00:42:07,817
Nobody wants to rip the two kingdoms
apart, least of all Aethelflaed.

463
00:42:09,318 --> 00:42:12,280
It is a path to peace.
And she would be safe.

464
00:42:16,284 --> 00:42:20,496
So, we have no conclusion
other than Edward has outwitted you.

465
00:42:21,122 --> 00:42:22,165
For now.

466
00:42:22,248 --> 00:42:24,125
So, he is as clever as his father.

467
00:42:25,001 --> 00:42:28,504
Which will be good for all Saxons,
including you.

468
00:42:35,386 --> 00:42:38,765
How did Cnut fall?
Was it his arrogance or his anger?

469
00:42:40,349 --> 00:42:44,187
Both, but mainly his betrayal.

470
00:42:45,188 --> 00:42:47,648
So, who did he murder
to further his ambition?

471
00:42:50,443 --> 00:42:52,862
He took Ragnar, who I loved,
and blamed another.

472
00:42:52,945 --> 00:42:56,365
Mm. The man had a reputation for cunning.

473
00:42:56,449 --> 00:42:58,034
I had always admired that.

474
00:42:59,118 --> 00:43:02,789
But he died dishonored,
if he allowed his woman to be enslaved.

475
00:43:03,539 --> 00:43:06,834
That was the work
of Uhtred the Dane Slayer.

476
00:43:08,586 --> 00:43:10,671
But I will have my revenge on him.

477
00:43:10,755 --> 00:43:13,591
I have heard of this Dane Slayer

478
00:43:13,674 --> 00:43:16,469
and what he has done
to our people for years.

479
00:43:21,432 --> 00:43:24,560
Why did Cnut not come
when we requested help?

480
00:43:25,978 --> 00:43:27,480
We had our own battles.

481
00:43:32,360 --> 00:43:33,402
What?

482
00:43:34,362 --> 00:43:37,782
- You escaped without our help.
- My kinsfolk did not.

483
00:43:39,242 --> 00:43:41,494
Our women and children
were murdered by the Irish

484
00:43:41,577 --> 00:43:43,121
before we had a chance to save them.

485
00:43:44,038 --> 00:43:46,207
Then you should avenge them
and make more children.

486
00:43:49,544 --> 00:43:50,753
Perhaps you're right.

487
00:43:52,296 --> 00:43:53,631
Grow strong here.

488
00:43:55,091 --> 00:43:59,720
Rest the men, get more silver,
then retake Dyflin.

489
00:44:03,015 --> 00:44:06,853
It seems empty, no?

490
00:44:07,562 --> 00:44:10,731
Yes, the greatest riches are in Wessex.

491
00:44:10,815 --> 00:44:13,192
Sadly, the Saxons do not like to share.

492
00:44:13,818 --> 00:44:16,988
And yet they say
their faith is based on love.

493
00:44:17,071 --> 00:44:18,489
They talk a lot of shit.

494
00:44:19,157 --> 00:44:22,618
More shit than the Irish?
This I can't believe.

495
00:44:22,702 --> 00:44:26,831
You have a lot to learn.
What are you gonna do for now?

496
00:44:26,914 --> 00:44:29,917
I'll cut off the head of this man
and send it to Hywel.

497
00:44:35,173 --> 00:44:37,216
It's just around the next corner.

498
00:44:37,300 --> 00:44:40,636
- Where are we going?
- It's a safer place to hide.

499
00:44:46,893 --> 00:44:47,935
Let's go.

500
00:44:52,690 --> 00:44:53,900
That's it. Go inside.

501
00:44:55,651 --> 00:44:56,736
Go.

502
00:44:59,530 --> 00:45:00,698
Stay there.

503
00:45:04,911 --> 00:45:07,371
Show me that child,
Father Pyrlig.

504
00:45:08,206 --> 00:45:09,749
Do not hide him from me.

505
00:45:17,882 --> 00:45:21,052
He is here?

506
00:45:21,677 --> 00:45:24,180
- You know about him?
- Indeed.

507
00:45:24,722 --> 00:45:28,309
I fear he had been taken, or lost forever.

508
00:45:32,146 --> 00:45:33,814
Did Uhtred bring him here?

509
00:45:34,899 --> 00:45:37,485
Apparently, even Aegelesburg
is better than the road.

510
00:45:37,568 --> 00:45:41,739
- Had quite the adventure by all accounts.
- Then I thank him for it.

511
00:45:41,822 --> 00:45:45,910
I know you dislike him,
but maybe Edward is right this time.

512
00:45:46,619 --> 00:45:48,913
Father Pyrlig, what have I not been told?

513
00:46:26,575 --> 00:46:29,203
There is a rumor
you have struck a bargain.

514
00:46:29,704 --> 00:46:30,746
Indeed.

515
00:46:31,664 --> 00:46:35,167
- I do not like the man.
- I do not need your approval.

516
00:46:35,251 --> 00:46:37,086
But it may be the only compromise.

517
00:46:37,169 --> 00:46:39,380
The Ealdormen will complain,

518
00:46:39,463 --> 00:46:42,091
but this time,
do not treat them too harshly.

519
00:46:43,342 --> 00:46:45,011
Then you will find some redemption.

520
00:46:45,094 --> 00:46:49,849
- I do not need redemption, either.
- Oh, my son, you do.

521
00:46:51,767 --> 00:46:53,519
If only for the sins of your mother.

522
00:47:05,156 --> 00:47:09,201
- Who is this?
- He is Aethelstan.

523
00:47:12,163 --> 00:47:13,789
He cannot be here.

524
00:47:13,873 --> 00:47:17,793
I know it is difficult
for you to acknowledge him,

525
00:47:17,877 --> 00:47:21,672
but I wondered,
now that certain threats are absent...

526
00:47:22,840 --> 00:47:25,885
perhaps the moment has come
for you to be reconciled.

527
00:47:25,968 --> 00:47:28,179
- Mother, I cannot.
- Please.

528
00:47:29,221 --> 00:47:33,559
He has lived a life of lies,
and that must be righted.

529
00:47:37,438 --> 00:47:43,027
I was wrong to wrench you apart,
and it's something that I deeply regret.

530
00:47:43,819 --> 00:47:49,116
I thought my past actions
were protecting you and Wessex,

531
00:47:49,200 --> 00:47:51,160
that I acted in the name of God.

532
00:47:51,744 --> 00:47:59,001
But God put love in your heart,
for your first wife and this child.

533
00:48:00,252 --> 00:48:02,129
And I should not have ignored that.

534
00:48:05,966 --> 00:48:09,512
So, I ask for your forgiveness...

535
00:48:10,805 --> 00:48:11,847
and his.

536
00:48:13,724 --> 00:48:16,143
He needs your protection.

537
00:48:25,236 --> 00:48:27,488
Place him back to where he was concealed.

538
00:49:19,665 --> 00:49:20,708
My King.

539
00:49:39,518 --> 00:49:42,229
- Have you made your choice?
- I will accept.

540
00:49:45,024 --> 00:49:47,026
If I can rule as my own man.

541
00:49:48,444 --> 00:49:52,364
I've never wanted to control Mercia.
Only see it at peace.

542
00:49:52,448 --> 00:49:54,825
Good, then we are of one mind.

543
00:49:56,410 --> 00:49:59,872
At long last, I strike a bargain
with Uhtred of Bebbanburg.

544
00:50:00,414 --> 00:50:04,919
That is a name from another life,
but yes, for now, we strike a bargain.

545
00:50:13,219 --> 00:50:14,261
Guards!

546
00:50:15,387 --> 00:50:17,556
Cenric, stand down your men.

547
00:50:18,057 --> 00:50:20,351
Lady, I cannot. The King forbids it.

548
00:50:20,768 --> 00:50:23,395
I am told
this is where my daughter's body is.

549
00:50:24,480 --> 00:50:26,649
This is where your King has led us.

550
00:50:27,399 --> 00:50:32,571
Cenric, please, in the name of Alfred,
open the gates and stand down your men.

551
00:50:42,206 --> 00:50:43,749
Open the gates!

552
00:51:00,975 --> 00:51:04,853
- Oh, my dearest girl, you've come home.
- Aelfwynn is dead.

553
00:51:04,937 --> 00:51:06,689
No, child.

554
00:51:06,772 --> 00:51:10,776
A miracle has occurred
and you are mistaken in your heartbreak.

555
00:51:21,912 --> 00:51:25,249
Mama?

556
00:51:49,273 --> 00:51:51,567
This night together!

557
00:51:51,650 --> 00:51:56,447
Oh, oh! Eh, eh! To Eadith,
for not killing the Lady Aelfwynn.

558
00:51:56,530 --> 00:51:58,616
- To Eadith!
- Yes/.

559
00:51:59,241 --> 00:52:02,828
Your brother has restored peace,
the people are being fed,

560
00:52:03,621 --> 00:52:05,039
and the fever passes.

561
00:52:05,497 --> 00:52:08,500
To Sihtric and Aethelflaed
and Young Uhtred, too.

562
00:52:08,584 --> 00:52:09,752
May they return safely.

563
00:52:10,336 --> 00:52:12,838
But if there's ale still left
when they get here,

564
00:52:12,921 --> 00:52:14,965
then we have let ourselves down.

565
00:52:19,637 --> 00:52:23,390
Mostly, everyone now looks
forward to the new Lord.

566
00:52:23,474 --> 00:52:25,017
Who is that to be?

567
00:52:26,352 --> 00:52:28,854
He has asked Uhtred.

568
00:52:31,857 --> 00:52:36,111
To the lands, to the silver
and to the women!

569
00:52:36,195 --> 00:52:38,697
To Uhtred of Mercia!

570
00:52:38,781 --> 00:52:40,866
Uhtred of Mercia!

571
00:52:43,202 --> 00:52:45,287
Finally, he can pay us some money!

572
00:52:45,371 --> 00:52:46,955
I very much doubt it.

573
00:52:46,979 --> 00:52:48,979
http://hiqve.com/

